      | l = \norm {a \oplus b}
      | o = \ne
      | r = 0
      | c = {{Defof|Normed Division Algebra}}: $\norm {a \oplus b} = \norm a \norm b$
}}
{{eqn | ll= \leadsto
      | l = a \oplus b
      | o = \ne
      | r = 0_A
      | c = {{Defof|Norm on Vector Space}}
}}
{{end-eqn}}
Thus for any arbitrary $a, b \ne 0_A$ we have shown that $a \oplus b \ne 0_A$.
Thus $A$ is a division algebra.
{{qed|lemma}}
