From the definition of a real Cauchy sequence it follows that $\sequence {\norm {x_n} }$ is a real Cauchy sequence in $\R$.
By Cauchy's Convergence Criterion on Real Numbers $\sequence {\norm {x_n} }$ has a limit in $\R$.
{{qed}}
\end{proof}

